Event Name: Yoga in the Park with Dianne Bondy
Club Name: Center for Social Justice Education and LGBT Communities (Rutgers University)
Event Description: A yoga practice for all bodies honoring the art of self-inquiry and compassonate self care followed by a lesson in exploring the concept of wellness for all. Learn how to be kinder to yourself, while employing new tools that help to make wellness and health a priority – regardless of any outstanding circumstances. By the end of this event, you will have tools and strategies to take better care of yourself with limited resources so that you can leave a positive impact on our communities and the world.

Club Name: Douglass Diversity and Inclusion Program at Douglass Residential College - DRC
Event Description: Please join us and come to an event hosted by the Douglass Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion Ambassadors! The ambassadors will present their semester-long research presentation where attendees will learn how the climate crisis and women's rights are interconnected, define what ecofeminism means, identify activists/poets who have been instrumental in the ecofeminist movement and what contributions they made to it, and understand at least one way that ecofeminism is relevant to today–be it politically, environmentally, economically, etc. Students should attend to learn about a topic that is not widely talked about during a crucial time - we are currently going through a climate crisis and the rights of women are being attacked. Learn how these two current problems intersect and what you can do about them.

Club Name: Seeing Eye Puppy Raising Club (Rutgers University)
Event Description: After a long hiatus, we are finally back to doing our annual destressor event at the Alexander Library on College Ave! We will be outside the library on the patio for this event. In case of rain, the rain date will be on the 4th at the same time, 2pm. At this event we allow stressed college students to pet the puppies as they prepare to take their finals. This event is a great opportunity to educate the public about our club and the mission of The Seeing Eye. Puppies will get ample practice with greeting people politely and calmly, and members will also get to practice handling the puppies and ensuring they are on their best behavior.

Event Name: 30th Annual Rites of Passage Ceremony Registration
Event Description: The annual Rites of Passage Ceremony is a pre-commencement celebration to honor Black and Latinx-identified students who through resolute persistence have successfully completed an undergraduate or graduate degree at Rutgers University—New Brunswick. The event recognizes their accomplishments, hard work, and dedication, while simultaneously acknowledging the accomplishments of our student’s families and networks of support. Distinguished speakers, student awards, performances, and the incorporation of African culture and traditions—specifically the culminating Kente Stole presentation—all add to the vibrancy of this celebratory day.

Event Name: Study Opportunity to watch brief coping videos to learn ways to effectively manage many challenges during the COVID-19 Era.
Event Description: Join a 12-week study to evaluate a quick way to learn how to effectively manage the many challenges as a Rutgers undergraduate in the COVID-19 era. Watch brief coping skills videos on your phone. Complete up to 4 surveys a day and 1 weekly survey (~5-20 minutes per day) on your phone for up to 6 weeks. https://kleimanlab.org/PhoneStudy
